  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Anne Knight acknowledges Maria Weston Chapman&apos;s kindness in sending &quot;so large a bounty to Paris.&quot; She praises the Christian action of American women and reflects that those women who &quot;have withdrawn from the ranks of justice I fear that they&quot; have been lacking in religious faith. Anne Knight&apos;s sister Maria and her husband John Candler are going to Jamaica to see how &quot;we as friends can best help the cause&quot; of the slave in the West Indies. Anne Knight requests that Mrs. Maria W. Chapman send information about American affairs.</subfield>
